@NODE Wuerfeln "Dice"

                                'Dice' - Gadget
                                ===============

   Pressing this gadget new numbers are created and the timer is started
   or not (depending on the @{" preferences " Link EinstZeit}

   The gadget is disabled / enabled automaticaly so that the user can't dice
   at the wrong time.

@ENDNODE

@NODE WuerfelnNN "Dice Again"

                             'Dice Again' - Gadget
                             =====================

   You only can see this gadget when you selected the option
   'Dice again' in the @{" preferences " Link EinstSonstiges}.

   Pressing it new numbers are created but the timer does continue to run!

   You also may define the quantity you can dice again. When you try to dice
   again too often you get the points you normally get after timeout.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Vorschlag "Suggestion"

                             'Suggestion' - Gadget
                             =====================

   This gadget is only available in level 1 thru 3.
   Otherwise you can get a suggestion from the computer.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Loesung "Solution"

                              'Solution' - Gadget
                              ===================

   When a player wants to know if his solution is the best solution he can
   use this gadget to get the very best solution.
   This gadget is only available when the option 'Show always solution' in
   the @{" preferences " Link EinstSonstiges} is NOT selected.
   By the way when the difference is 0 it doesn't make much sense to ask
   for a solution.

@ENDNODE

@NODE NeuesSpiel "A new game"

                              'New Game' - Gadget
                              ===================

   Pressing this gadget the listwiev is cleared and new numbers are
   generated in case you selected the option chance in the
   @{" preferences " Link EinstZahlen}.
   What does stay the same are the players names, the level, the kind of
   the animation, the timer and the quantity of the numbers.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Einstellungen "Preferences"

                             'Preferences' - Gadget
                             ======================

   The preferences window is opened.

   @{" Preferences window " Link Einstellungsfenster}

@ENDNODE

@NODE Ende "What the hell does this gadget"

                                'Quit' - Gadget
                                ===============

   Ehm, well if you don't know what this gadget does you should consider to turn
   off your computer and send it to me!!!

@ENDNODE

@NODE DeineLoesung "Your Solution"

                                'Your Solution'
                                ===============

   Here you can enter your solution. Only numbers from 0 to 9, +, -, *, / and
   brackets are accepted.

   For mouse-men we built a @{" calculator " Link Taschenrechner} popup window where the actual
   numbers can be choosen with the mouse.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Taschenrechner "Calculator"

                                   Calculator
                                   ==========

   Here you can choose the actual numbers and the number * 10, 100 and 1000
   with the mouse.
   You also can choose the operators. When you make a mistake you can clear
   an character with '<-'.
   Pressing 'OK' is the same as entering <RETURN> in the string gadget.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Zeit "Remaining Time"

                                'Remaining Time'
                                ================

   Here you can see the remaining time you have to enter your solution.
   You can change it in the @{" preferences " Link EinstZeit}.
   When the time is over you get some punischment points and it's the next
   players turn.

@ENDNODE

