@NODE EinstSpieler "Players"

                                    Players
                                    =======

   Here you can

      first define how many players should play (up to eight)
      using the slider,

      second define the names of the players using the string gadget and

      third define how many players should be simulated by the amiga using
      the checkbox. When you select the checkbox there appears a ' C= '
      in the first row of the listview which stands for Commodore.


@ENDNODE

@NODE EinstZahlen "Numbers"

                                    Numbers
                                    =======

   First you select how many numbers you want to have (using the slider).
   When you select 'chance' the numbers are generated randomly
   otherwise consecutive numbers are generated.

   Examlpe

         Chance is slected:         Chance is not selected:

            1  -->  54                     1  -->  1
            2  -->  66                     2  -->  2
            3  -->  27                     3  -->  3
                     .                              .
                     .                              .
                     .                              .



@ENDNODE

@NODE EinstZeit "Timer"

                                     Timer
                                     =====

   This option makes the game much more interisting. When you select it
   you have to enter your solution before the time is over.
   Furthermore you can define the amount of time and the amount of ponts
   you get after timeout.

@ENDNODE

@NODE EinstWuerfel "Dice"

                                      Dice
                                      ====

   If the checkmark 'Show animations' is selected you get some
   nice animations whenever you press @{" Dice " Link Wuerfeln} or @{" Dice again " Link WuerfelnNN}
   Furthermore you can choose one of six kinds of animations.
   Note: If you have a 68000 you better disable this option.

@ENDNODE

@NODE EinstSonstiges "Misc"

                                      Misc
                                      ====

   Level:

   Here you can choose one of the five levels.


   Show always the solution:

   When the checkmark is selected you get the best solution after you
   entered your solution (only if the difference is not 0)


   Display popup as normal window:

   If you like to move the calculator popup window and if you want it to
   stay opended choose this option.


   Dice again:

   Here you can select if you want to have the possibility to dice again.
   Furthermore you can define how often you like to dice again.


   Use calculator:

   Here you have the possibility to define an external program
   (e.g. SYS:Tools/Calculator) when you are not so familiar with
   maths.

@ENDNODE

@NODE EinstSpeichern "Save"

                                      Save
                                      ====

   When pressing this button the preferences are saved under

   ENVARC:Schlawiner.prefs

   Furthermore the window is closed and you can start a new game.

@ENDNODE

@NODE EinstBenutzen "Use"

                                      Use
                                      ===

